- Option (a) describes one condition: Pat experiences excessive hunger.

In probability, the likelihood of two events both occurring (in this case, excessive hunger and acidity) is generally less than or equal to the likelihood of either event occurring on its own. Given this principle, the more probable option is:
(a) They also experience excessive hunger.
